place.name: FISHLEY
place.gazetteerText: FISHLEY, a parish in Blofield district, Norfolk; near the river Buire, 4 miles NNE of Buckenham r. station, and 11 E of Norwich. Post town, Acle, under Norwich. Acres, 476. Real property, £1, 666. Pop., 10. House, 1. The property is chiefly in one estate. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £141. Patron, Miss Edwards. The church is old but good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
